Primorye is ready to accommodate refugees from Donbass in 14 temporary centers
20 February 2022, 08:58
Photo: ©
"Izvestia"/Kristina Kormilitsina
Read ren.tv in
Residents of the self-proclaimed Donetsk and Lugansk republics in Primorye are ready to be placed in 14 temporary accommodation centers. The governor's press secretary, Makar Rudenchik, told RIA Novosti.
“In the event of the arrival of refugees from the DPR and LPR in Primorye, the region is ready to deploy fourteen temporary accommodation points,” -
he said.
According to Rudenchik, TAPs are located in different municipalities of the region on the basis of sanatoriums, recreation centers and hostels.
He also noted that so far there has been no information about the arrival of refugees, but the regional government has already taken measures to receive them.
The Jewish Autonomous Region is ready to accommodate refugees from Donbass in six temporary centers
Expand
20 February 2022, 05:58
February 17 in LPR
stated
about the aggravation of the situation on the contact line. The same information came from the DPR. They noted that the Armed Forces of Ukraine 15 times since the beginning of the day
violated the "silence regime".
On February 18, the head of the DPR Denis Pushilin said that Ukrainian troops are ready for an offensive in the Donbass. Heads of the DPR and LPR
announced
about the beginning of mass evacuation of the population to Russia. Head of the LPR Leonid Pasechnik
called
men capable of holding weapons in their hands and defending their land. According to the People's Militia of the DPR, Ukraine attempted three sabotage attempts that day.
In Russia, the Rostov region accepts most of the refugees - temporary accommodation centers have been created there.
Let us recall that Ukraine’s military operation against the DPR and LPR began in 2014, after the regions declared independence in connection with the coup d’etat in the country. According to the UN, about 13 thousand people became victims of the clash.
