Home
News
in the world
Putin: Pumping up arms provokes Kiev to use force in Donbass
20 February 2022, 17:46
Photo: ©
ministryofdefenceua
Read ren.tv in
Pumping up Kyiv with weapons provokes Ukraine to make a forceful decision in Donbass. Russian President Vladimir Putin stated this in a telephone conversation with French leader Emmanuel Macron, the Kremlin press service reports.
Thus, Putin drew Macron’s attention to the ongoing pumping of Ukraine with the latest weapons and ammunition by NATO states.
According to Putin, this is pushing Ukraine towards a military solution to the situation in Donbass. The President of Russia believes that because of this, citizens of the DPR and LPR are suffering, who are evacuating to Russia to escape shelling.
Putin called the provocations of the Ukrainian military the reason for the escalation in Donbass
Expand
20 February 2022, 17:27
February 17 in LPR
stated
about the aggravation of the situation on the contact line. The same information came from the DPR. They noted that the Armed Forces of Ukraine 15 times since the beginning of the day
violated the "silence regime".
On February 18, the head of the DPR Denis Pushilin said that Ukrainian troops are ready for an offensive in the Donbass. February 19, heads of the DPR and LPR
announced
general mobilization.
As of February 20, after
announced
On February 18, the heads of the DPR and LPR temporarily evacuated more than 40 thousand refugees to Russia
arrived in the Rostov region from Donbass.
Later 26 regions of Russia
declared their readiness to accept refugees
in temporary accommodation centers. About 2 thousand refugees were taken by train from the Rostov region to the Voronezh and Kursk regions.
Let us recall that Ukraine’s military operation against the DPR and LPR began in 2014, after the regions declared independence in connection with the coup d’etat in the country. According to the UN, about 13 thousand people became victims of the clash.
